    "number": 1347,
    "title": "Found a bug: pagination skips the last page when per_page divides evenly",
    "state": "open",
    "state_reason": null,
    "body": "## Description\n\nI'm having a problem with this.\n\nWhen the total number of results is an exact multiple of `per_page`, the client appears to skip fetching the final page because the `Link` header omits a `next` rel even though there is one more empty page.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a repo with exactly 60 open issues.\n2. Request `GET /repos/octocat/Hello-World/issues?per_page=30&page=2`.\n3. Observe that the `Link` header does not include `rel=\"next\"`.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nThe API should be consistent about when `next` is emitted.\n\n## Environment\n\n- octokit.js: `3.1.2`\n- node: `20.11.0`\n- OS: macOS 14.2\n\n```js\nconst { data } = await octokit.rest.issues.listForRepo({\n  owner: 'octocat',\n  repo: 'Hello-World',\n  per_page: 30,\n  page: 2\n});\nconsole.log(data.length); // 30, but no next link\n```\n\nThanks in advance for any help!",
